# Verification Loop

Run this checklist after completing a feature or significant change, before creating a PR.

## Phases

### Phase 1: Build

```bash
npm run build
```

If build fails, stop and fix before continuing.

### Phase 2: Type Check

```bash
npx tsc --noEmit
```

Fix all type errors. Zero tolerance.

### Phase 3: Lint

```bash
npm run lint
```

Fix errors; warnings are acceptable if pre-existing.

### Phase 4: Tests

```bash
npm test
```

All tests must pass. If a test fails:
1. Check if the failure is from your change or pre-existing
2. Fix your change if it caused the failure
3. Never delete or skip a test to make the suite pass

### Phase 5: Security Scan

Quick checks on changed files:

- No hardcoded secrets (`sk-`, `ghp_`, `AKIA`, password literals)
- No `console.log` of sensitive data
- Auth checks present on protected API routes
- Prisma queries use parameterized inputs (default with Prisma ORM)

**Automation gaps:** This phase is manual. Automated secret scanning and security linting are not configured. To strengthen it:

- Add security-focused ESLint plugins (e.g. `eslint-plugin-security`, `eslint-plugin-no-secrets`) in `eslint.config.mjs`
- Enable a pre-commit hook (e.g. husky) for secret scanning
- Add a CI job for secret scanning (e.g. Gitleaks, TruffleHog)

### Phase 6: Diff Review

```bash
git diff --stat
```

Review each changed file for:
- Unintended changes (formatting-only diffs, accidental file modifications)
- Missing error handling in new code paths
- Missing Sentry instrumentation in new catch blocks
- Dutch strings for all user-facing messages

### Phase 7: PR-reviewthreads (CodeRabbit e.d.)

Als je een PR bijwerkt na **CodeRabbit**- of andere inline review-opmerkingen:

1. Los de opmerkingen in de code op en push; wacht tot CI groen is waar relevant.
2. Zet daarna de bijbehorende **reviewthreads op GitHub op Resolved** (niet alleen “gefixt in code” — de thread moet dicht). Bijvoorbeeld: GraphQL-mutatie `resolveReviewThread` via `gh api graphql` met de thread-`id` uit de PR.

Zonder deze stap blijven opmerkingen open staan terwijl de fix al op de branch staat.

## Report Format

After running all phases:

```
VERIFICATION REPORT
==================
Build:     [PASS/FAIL]
Types:     [PASS/FAIL] (X errors)
Lint:      [PASS/FAIL] (X warnings)
Tests:     [PASS/FAIL] (X/Y passed)
Security:  [PASS/FAIL] (X issues)
Diff:      X files changed
PR threads: [N/A / RESOLVED] (CodeRabbit & co. na fix)

Overall:   [READY/NOT READY] for PR
```

## When to Run

- After completing a feature branch
- Before opening or updating a PR
- After resolving merge conflicts
- After a major refactor
